Hacking stuff to get Delphes to run in parallel:

Step 1) Copy TTask.h to $ROOTSYS/core/base/inc/
Step 2) Copy TTask.cxx to $ROOTSYS/core/base/src/
Step 3) Go to your root directory (cd $ROOTSYS) and 'make'
        (Don't worry. I made absolutely sure that my hacks did not break ROOT.)
Step 4) You may need to install Delphes 3.0.7 just to be sure of compatibility.
Step 5) Copy ExRootTask.cc to $DELPHESDIR/external/ExRootAnalysis/
Step 6) Go to your Delphes directory (cd $DELPHESDIR) and 'make'
Step 7) Come back to the gambit/modules/HEColliderBit/src directory.
Step 8) Use the makefile here to make 'example-delphes-py8'. Which now runs in parallel.
Step 9) Enjoy.

--Abram
